results.name: Number of solutions to gcd(x^2 + y^2 + z^2 + t^2 + h^2, n) = 1 with x,y,z,t,h in [0,n-1].
link: Amiram Eldar, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
formula: a(n) = phi(n^5) = n^4 * phi(n), where phi=A000010.
Dirichlet g.f.: zeta(s - 5) / zeta(s - 4). The n-th term of the Dirichlet inverse is n^4 * A023900(n) = (-1)^omega(n) * a(n) / A003557(n), where omega = A001221.
Sum_{k=1..n} a(k) ~ n^6 / Pi^2. - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Feb 02 2019
results.author: _José María Grau Ribas_, Feb 28 2014
